(2515, 292, 'Make equipment type editing live', 1, 102, 1, 1, '2012-01-01 20:38:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-01-03', '2012-12-16', 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'You can log in to the Vine and then switch to the page. It should use the same session so the login should be interchangeable.\r\n\r\n1. Add a ReadEventTypeList() function to VineDB to read the event type list.\r\n2. Make the list on equipmenttypes.php show records from the equipmenttype table and make the edit link provide a link to an equipmenttype record to the editing page. \r\n3. Make editequipmenttype.php show the name based on a lookup in the equipmenttype table using the passed id.\r\n4. Make the name field required if it is not already (look at the class documentation in tools.nth-generation.com for instructions on this.\r\n5. Save new and edited records using stored procedures in Equipment.sql. Implement this in the style used in the charity shopper business and charity pages.\r\n6. Show error messages using the $form->ShowFormErrors(); function already on the page.\r\n7. In case of success forward back to the equipmenttypes.php page.'),
(2516, 278, 'Make a login page.', 1, 102, 1, 1, '2012-01-01 20:48:56', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-01-01', '2012-12-16', 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'Facilities shares the same database as Vine, Discoveryland and SU. \r\n\r\nI added a VineDB.php to the project which has the same login functions as Vine. It is probably easiest therefore to make the login page a copy of the Vine login page and do pretty much the same thing as that login. \r\n\r\nMinimally you will need to make these changes:\r\n\r\n1. Change the page title to indicate that you are logging in to the Vine facilities site instead of the Vine site. \r\n2. After a successful login go to the pendingevents.php page.'),
(2517, 292, 'Make equipment editing live', 1, 102, 1, 1, '2012-01-01 21:02:58', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-01-03', '2012-12-16', 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'You can log in to the Vine and then switch to the page. It should use the same session so the login should be interchangeable.\r\n\r\n1. Make the list on equipmentlist.php show records from the equipment table and make the edit link provide a link to an equipment record to the editing page. \r\nMake the equipment type drop down list on addeditequipment.php live.\r\n3. Make addeditequipment.php show the equipmwent fields based on a lookup in the equipment table using the passed id.\r\n4. Show the required field message implemented in the FacilityFormClass class.\r\n5. Save new and edited records using stored procedures in Equipment.sql. Implement this in the style used in the charity shopper business and charity pages.\r\n6. Show error messages using the $form->ShowFormErrors(); function already on the page.\r\n7. In case of success forward back to theequipmentlist.php page.'),
