(2593, 306, 'Activation page', 1, 145, 1, 1, '2012-01-11 19:26:09', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-01-12', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'Build a page where someone can activate their account. The address for it should be like this:\r\n\r\nhttp://percmobileserver.aegidagroup.com/Welcome/activate/XXXXXXXXXXX\r\n\r\nwhere XXXXXXXXXXX is the actual activation key.\r\n\r\nYou can get the activation key off of the url using $this->uri->segment(n).\r\n\r\nYou can read about it here:\r\n\r\nhttp://codeigniter.com/user_guide/libraries/uri.html\r\n\r\nThe activation page should like like the 1st page of fetching a lost password in that there will only be 1 input field, in this case a password.\r\n\r\nThere should only be 1 button which is to submit the password and log in. There should be no cancel or back button.\r\n\r\nIf activation is successful you should forward them to a page where they can change their password. If it is not successful then you should just show an error message.\r\n\r\nThis is the store procedure to activate a page:\r\n\r\nActivateWebAccount (\r\n	i_actkey	varchar(80),\r\n    i_password	varchar(64)\r\n)'),
