(2635, 278, 'Make pending events list page live', 1, 102, 1, 1, '2012-01-19 03:42:11', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-02-08', '2012-12-16', 'Queued', NULL, NULL, '1. There are new fields in the eventdate table: approvedon, rejectedon, requestedon. Add them to the eventdatename view (eventdatedesc.sql).\r\n\r\n2. List all future event dates where approvedon is null. Query the eventdatename view joined to the activitytype view. activitytype is needed for the activity type column. \r\n\r\nYou want to include all future dates where requestedon is not null and approved on and rejectedon are both null.\r\n\r\n3. The list should be sorted in order of the event date.\r\n\r\n4. Show the dates in Jan 1, 2012 format. You can do this most easily with the mysql format_date() function.'),
(2636, 277, 'New procedures: ApproveEvent, RejectEvent', 1, 102, 1, 1, '2012-01-19 03:46:39', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-01-24', '2012-12-16', 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'Make a new module in sql/procedures: EventStatus.sql\r\n\r\nAdd these procedures:\r\n\r\nApproveEvent\r\nSet approvedon=now() and rejectedon=null\r\n\r\nRejectEvent\r\nSet approvedon=null and rejectedon=now()\r\n\r\n\r\nI have adopted a new method of building stored procedures that uses a lot of error checking and also indicates error conditions by setting the @err variable in mysql. \r\n\r\nYou can use the existing facilities stored procedures as an example. Do your best to follow this and we will discuss it when you are finished.'),
(2637, 278, 'Add drop down lists to the create event page', 1, 104, 1, 1, '2012-01-19 03:54:24', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-02-08', '2012-12-16', 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'The following fields should be drop down lists:\r\n\r\nStatus (correct as it is)\r\n\r\nEvent Type: Copy the FillActivityTypeList() function from vinedb.php in the vine project into the database class that juluis created for this project (ask him).\r\n\r\nStaff Contact: We have several pages in the Vine project where we ask for a staff person to be selected (for example group and event editing). Copy whatever function is creating that list into this project.\r\n\r\nAssociated group: Add this to the database class to fill that list:\r\n\r\nfunction FillOrganizationGroupList($id) {\r\n	$this->FillList("select  ga.grpid, g.name from groupactivities ga join groups g on ga.grpid=g.grpid where ga.activityid=16 order by name", $id);\r\n}'),
(2638, 278, 'Fill in live data in the event info page', 1, NULL, 1, 1, '2012-01-19 03:58:54', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-10-31', '2012-12-16', 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'Fill in as many of the fields as you can find. You can probably get most of them by querying the eventdatedesc view. \r\n\r\nThe following fields can be removed from the page (comment them out in case we need to add them back):\r\n\r\nPolice Detail\r\nCalendars\r\n\r\nI think there is a single field for notes and description so you can probably remove one of them.'),
(2639, 278, 'Implement building / room selection on add room page', 1, NULL, 1, 1, '2012-01-19 04:04:15', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-05-11', '2012-12-16', 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'You have to pick a building, then fill the list of rooms based on the building selected. \r\n\r\nI''m thinking the best way to do this is actually NOT with jquery. There are only a couple of buildings so it may be easier just to have php build javascript arrays for the rooms in each building. Then when a building is selected use javascript to fill the drop down list with the rooms matching the building id. \r\n\r\nDoes this make sense? If not ask me.'),
