(2704, 141, 'Label printing formatting - 238', 1, 102, 1, 1, '2012-02-09 02:16:22', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-02-10', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'This really applies to both self check in and visitor checking but I think it is the same page that is shared between them (or at least it should be the same page).\r\n\r\nI am forwarding an illustration of what they are getting and also what they should be getting. \r\n\r\nThe size of the label seems to be correct, just maybe font sizes and placement.\r\n\r\nAnd the notes and allergies need to be on the left margin, not aligned below the service time.'),
(2705, 141, 'Printing the wrong label - 319', 1, 102, 1, 1, '2012-02-09 02:28:02', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-02-13', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'This is what they wrote:\r\n\r\nWe checked in a child, I  think his name was fwoopy on the self checkin.\r\n The label that printed out was for Jose Rodriguez, who happens to work for  the CIA.  He got the security code 3433. On the room checkin, he did not  show up, but Fwoopy did show up. It is an off bug to say the least.\r\n\r\nThis is my theory...\r\nIt looks like you are passing the ids to the label printing page and then the label printing page is using this query to find the student info:\r\n\r\nSELECT id, firstname, lastname, grade, allergies FROM membernames WHERE id =''.$cid[$cnt].'' union SELECT id, firstname, lastname, grade, NULL FROM childguests WHERE id =''.$cid[$cnt]\r\n\r\nThe problem is that guests and real children are stored in different tables and there are probably overlapping id numbers in the 2 tables. I''m guessing this is why the wrong kid printed.\r\n\r\nThere should be a function in the json server that looks up a kid''s info from the security number (ListCheckedInHouseholdMembers I think). That is what you need to be using. You may need to add a couple fields to it to get everything you need to print the label.'),
