(2712, 196, 'New Home page editor - category editing', 1, 102, 1, 1, '2012-02-11 18:30:46', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-02-22', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'We need a page similar to http://www.tests.com/dbadmin/homepageeditor.php or http://www.tests.com/dbadmin/homepageeditor2.php for editing the new home page (http://www.tests.com/index2012.php).\r\n\r\nI want to do this on 2 different pages. 1 for editing all of the single fields like page title, page description, meta tags, etc... I want a second page for editing the menu tree under Find Tests.\r\n\r\nThis task is related to the menu tree under Find Tests.\r\n\r\nIf you click the links under Find Tests you will see different pop ups with links in them. The link editing is similar to the link editing on the old home page editor homepageeditor.php\r\n\r\nIn addition to the list of links the fields that we need to edit for each section are:\r\n\r\nTitle\r\nColumns\r\nVertical Position\r\n\r\nAt this point he is not asking for color editing. \r\n\r\nDO NOT include the fields at the bottom for things like html description, meta description, page description... We will do all of those on a separate page.\r\n\r\nI have created a new table homepage3menu for this. We want to store the list of links as a single text field and allow him to use html editing to edit the list (like homepageeditor2.php). \r\n\r\nIn this case there are no columns as the page is not laid out in a grid. We just need to be able to order the list using the posn field in the table and also add, remove and hide records (hide using the visible field).'),
