(2716, 310, 'Change of plan', 1, 1, 1, 2, '2012-02-13 19:33:23', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-03-06', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, '2 types are possible (individually or together):\r\nNumber of subscribers\r\nLength of subscription\r\n\r\nDowngrade:  User is already paid through the next billing cycle.  User must select which profiles to delete, upon completion user is immediately downgraded.  User billing is not changed until next billing cycle, at which point they are billed at the lower rate.  No refunds for remaining time on the old plan are issued (eg: not prorated).\r\n\r\nMonthly Upgrade:  User is already paid for the lower plan through the next billing cycle.  User selects to upgrade and is immediately upgraded.  Billing is not changed until the next billing cycle, at which point they are billed at the higher rate.  As a user courtesy, they receive the new service for the remaining billing period for free.\r\n\r\nYearly Upgrade:  User is immediately upgraded by renewing their annual contract for another year at that annual subscription price.  The charge is offset by prorating their remaining time in the system.  Eg.  if they have 200 days left in their subscription when they upgrade, they will renew their subscription at the upgraded plan price going rate, which will renew them for another year.  They will also be credited to that upgrade price the money they already paid - $$ divided by 365 multiplied by 200.  Whole days only are pro-rated.'),
(2717, 293, 'Cancel plan', 1, 1, 1, 2, '2012-02-13 19:39:43', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-03-19', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'User is already paid through the next billing cycle.  When user cancels, users profile information is deleted (after at least two warning click-throughs) BUT users overall account is still active for another XX days (30? 60? 90?) so that they can re-subscribe if they desire.  After the account expiration is reached, the account and all remaining associated data is deleted and they dont exist on the system at all anymore.  We retain basic billing information for later charge disputes, etc.'),
