(2769, 311, 'Access level should be hard coded into the stored procedure', 1, 145, 1, 3, '2012-02-27 16:20:52', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-02-28', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'DisableMobileDeviceSupport and EnableMobileDeviceSupport both have a level (i_level) passed to them. I assume this is the access level required to enable or disable a device. We want to have the required level built into the procedure, not passed from the page.\r\n\r\nWe may at some point have all of that stored in a table but for now we want to just hard code it into the procedures.\r\n\r\nYou should change any other places where this type of thing is done in the support site.'),
(2771, 311, 'Use phone number to disable device', 1, 145, 1, 2, '2012-02-27 18:34:43', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-02-27', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'The stored procedure to disable a device has been changed to expect a phone number instead of a rowid. You''ll need to change the page to pass a phone number.'),
