(2808, 249, 'Mock up a Simple Administrative website', 1, 104, 1, 1, '2012-03-08 17:54:53', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-03-14', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'I need a very simple administrative web site for dailyverse.net. The user interface can be very basic because it will only be used by me and maybe some researchers. What I am say is there is no reason to spend a lot of time on making the site look nice.\r\n\r\nDo not upload this to the server. Just build it on your own computer and then send me a zip file when you are finished.\r\n\r\nYou could rip off the cms site or the project manager or the dancebits song cms or anything else like that.\r\n\r\nThe pages needed initially are:\r\n\r\n1. Login page\r\n2. Some sort of home page. I don''t know what we will end up putting on it. It is really just a a landing page after logging in that provides access to the menu options.\r\n3. A page to edit the list of quote types (Movie lines, bible verses, phylosophy, self help....). The only fields there are name and an active/inactive check box. This should have a page that lists the current types and an indication of which are active or inactive. There needs to be a button to add a new one which launches a new page to do the input.\r\n3. A page for editing authors. This should work a lot like step 2. For now we just need to enter the name. But you might as well add a field for dates (something like "1822 - 1895" in a single text input field and bio (a single text area field).\r\n4. A page for input of quotes. there needs to be a drop down list to select the author and a text area to enter the quote and a submit button. The submit button goes to step 5...\r\n5. After the submit the quote instead of just saving it I want to check the database to see if it is already there. This page should list the author at the top followed by the qoute just entered. Below that should be a list of similar quotes. There should be a button to add the quote and a button to cancel addition and go back to the page in step 4.\r\n6. Probably somewhere on the page that lists the authors there ought to be a button or link that will load a page that will list the quotes for a specific author (so a button or link next to each name in the list). The author quote list page just needs to list all of the quotes. Each quote should be a link that loads the page into an editor. \r\n7. The quote editor page should have the same fields as the page for input of a quote (step 4) except the buttons are Update and Delete and Cancel (Cancel goes back to the list of quotes in step 6).'),
(2809, 311, 'Edit subscription options', 1, 145, 1, 2, '2012-03-09 14:44:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-03-12', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'A support person needs to have the option to:\r\n\r\n1. Select a different plan\r\n2. End a subscription\r\n\r\nSelecting a different plan will have the same constraints that it has in the public web site as far as what plans you can change to. Ideally we can place most of that logic into libraries or helpers that are shareable between the 2 sites.\r\n\r\nTake a look at this and then let''s discuss your ideas before you implement anything.\r\n\r\nYou can''t really implement the actual closing of the account because it will involve some paypal interactions (we need to cancel their billing) so just build this up to the point where we do the cancellation. Then talk to me about that also.'),
(2810, 311, 'Add a missed payment', 1, 135, 1, 4, '2012-03-09 14:45:36', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-07-11', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'There is a possibility that a payment could go thru paypal but not be recorded in our system. We need to have a way of getting the payment history from paypal (already listed as a separate task) and then record the payment in our db.'),
(2811, 311, 'Make a payment', 1, 145, 1, 2, '2012-03-09 14:53:58', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-03-09', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'Someone may contact support because their account has been cancelled. We need to have a page where they can take a payment over the phone and reactivate the account. \r\n\r\n1. We need to have a button to reactivate a closed account.\r\n\r\nThis will be grouped with the "Edit Subscription" button. CLick the button and it gives you two options, pay or change subscription. \r\n\r\n2. There needs to be a page that explains the terms of the reactivation (for instance they have to pay the fees from the termination date up to today). There should be an "Activate" button from here to start the activation.\r\n-----------\r\n3. From there we need to launch paypal. I''m not sure how this will work so you probably need to stop after step 2.\r\n\r\nCan you think of anything else?'),
(2812, 311, 'Resetting Email And Password', 145, 145, 145, 1, '2012-03-09 16:14:35', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-03-09', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'When clicking reset account, their should be two options, one to just reset their password and another to reset both their password and email and have the password sent to their new email.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n---Also shows the email in the paragraph above the options so support can verify correct email address on file.'),
(2813, 181, 'Merge Fixes', 1, NULL, 1, 1, '2012-03-09 18:46:21', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'See the pdf that I sent to your email.\r\n\r\nTalk to me about how much of this is finished ASAP.'),
(2814, 308, 'Clean up use of PushArrowsName', 1, NULL, 1, 3, '2012-03-11 16:50:07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-04-04', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'This should probably be called from inside the helpers, either  from the section headings or from the tab helper. \r\n\r\nIt might also be possible to do this from the ShowEditTab function and function for showing privacy icons\r\n\r\nRegardless if we are going to be creating Arrow ID''s from different places then we need a helper to do that consistently.'),
