(2821, 141, 'Not all labels printed when adding a sibling - 359', 1, 104, 1, 1, '2012-03-12 13:16:16', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-03-29', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'add 2nd sibling..the sibling that is added prints, but not the original child\r\n\r\nMR: I suspect that this has to do with the arrangement of the labels on the page. If you check in a bunch of people at one time you will notice that the labels are not all stacked vertically. Some are stacked vertically and soe are side by side. I don''t know if this will eect the printing or not. \r\n\r\nThink about it to see if you have a different idea and then talk to me about it. I am probably going to have to go there and fix it on site but I would like to have an idea how to go about it before I get there.'),
(2822, 141, 'Capitalization - 360', 1, 102, 1, 1, '2012-03-12 13:17:31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-03-13', '2012-03-14', 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'siblings and guests should have 1st letter capitalized and rest lower case.\r\n\r\nWe have code in the charity shopper project that will do capitalization. I will email it to you.'),
(2824, 141, 'Not printing some labels - 319', 1, NULL, 1, 1, '2012-03-12 13:28:04', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-04-01', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'V: We checked in a child, I think his name was fwoopy on the self checkin. The label that printed out was for Jose Rodriguez, who happens to work for the CIA. He got the security code 3433. On the room checkin, he did not show up, but Fwoopy did show up. It is an off bug to say the least. \r\n\r\nMR: We had a hard time recreating this but I did find something in the code that could cause it. We made that correction but we are not 100% sure that the bug is fixed because we could not recreate it.\r\n\r\nV: While Jose is not showing up, when you try and adding fwoop as a guest his tag does not print at all.'),
