(2832, 311, 'Pay / reactivate', 1, 145, 1, 2, '2012-03-13 15:17:50', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-03-14', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'The Payment/Reactivate option should only be available if the subscription is expired (expires on date is past).\r\n\r\nWe need to have a page that is available when you click the Payment/Reactivate button that explains what will happen and how. Something like:\r\n\r\nThe account expired 65 days ago. In order to reactivate the account the client must pay for 2 months to make the account current ($25.00) in addition to the charge for the current month. \r\n\r\nThen we should ask them which plan they want to use to reactivate the account. They may choose any plan. It should default to the plan that was in effect before they expired. If they choose a plan that has fewer profiles than what they currently have they need to indicate who to remove from their subscription. You will need to add a page or a hidden div that lets the support person do this.\r\n\r\nAfter this they need to click a button that actually implements the reactivation which would mean getting a credit card payment. Add the button to the page but don''t make it actually do anything. Don''t implement any database updates yet, just mock up the pages with live data. I have a feeling the flow is likely to change.'),
