(2927, 323, 'Software should check the db schema version', 1, NULL, 1, 2, '2012-05-07 14:50:35', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-06-26', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'The application should check the db schema version to see if it is supported. If it is not supported then the software may not be able to continue. Because we can not anticipate what schema changes will happen the min software version needs to be in a database field so that the application can check against itself. \r\n\r\nThere are 3 possibilities\r\n1. Fully supported\r\n2. Compatible but not fully supported\r\n3. Incompatible'),
(2928, 308, 'Allows most features on an expired account', 1, 145, 1, 1, '2012-05-09 15:13:52', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-06-08', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'I think they can probably view but not edit info or activate anything.\r\n\r\nThey should be able to renew their subscription or cancel their subscription or do anything related to payments. Those are probably the only functions that should be working.\r\n\r\nIf we are not doing it already we should probably show a page on login that explains that their account is expired and ask them if they want to renew their subscription. This will most likely happen because someone''s credit card was not successfully charged so let''s just start with that as an explanation. They can either go directly to the subscription page or they can go into the regular site with all edits disabled.\r\n\r\nLet''s talk about what is the best way to implement this in the class.\r\n\r\n\r\n****RenewSession() will now return a unique error code (9999) if subscription is expired.*****'),
