(2955, 278, 'Formatting on Event page', 1, 104, 1, 2, '2012-05-15 01:11:42', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-05-16', '2012-05-21', 'Queued', NULL, NULL, '1. Add a right justified link in the blue bar at the top (the one that says "GET THE FACTS! from USCIS"). Call the link "Edit" and make it go to editevent.php. \r\n2. The alignment in the table below the blue bar is a little off. The labels in the left column are not aligned with the data in the right column.\r\n3. Remove "Police Detail I do NOT need a policeman at my event" along with the arrow that follows it..\r\n4. Format "Catering Kitchen I do NOT plan on using the catering Kitchen for my event" like the rest of the info in this section with "Catering Kitchen" as the label and the rest as the data.\r\n\r\nActually steps 2-4 of tjhe page should look like this: eventrecurrances.php'),
(2956, 278, 'Logging in redirects t a prior page from a prior session', 1, 104, 1, 1, '2012-05-15 01:32:02', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-05-24', '2012-12-16', 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'I think there is probably a session variable or something that saving the prior page or next page. If you put some debug statements in  and stop the page from redirecting so you can read them you should be able to figure it out. \r\n\r\nWhatever variable is being used, we just need to clear it on a new login I think.'),
(2957, 327, 'Editing an emergency contact that is not your is odd', 1, NULL, 1, 2, '2012-05-15 15:51:44', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-06-06', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, '1. It requires the priority field\r\n2. It gives an error trying to save\r\n\r\nIt did save the contact fields once I put in a priority. It probably gave the update error trying to update profileemergencycontacts.\r\n\r\nFixes:\r\n\r\n1. Priority is only required if the contact is for the person being edited (profile id has a value)\r\n2. If the priority is only required if we have a profile id\r\n3. If we have no profile id but a priority is given then we need to add the contact to the profile.'),
