(2962, 181, 'Merge page changes', 1, 104, 1, 1, '2012-05-18 02:33:29', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-05-24', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, '1. The Website Login label does not align with the others.\r\n2. Add a field in the "General" section labelled "Congregation". Put it between the name and the address.\r\n3. Put some sort of dummy data in each field, even if it is just an X.\r\n4. Email address should not be bold.\r\n5. The X for No Email shoudl not be bold and it should not be a link.\r\n6. Replace all of the "Use These" with radio buttons. The purpose of each radio button is to indicate which column will be used for each section. So for instance in the section that has gender, language and marital status you are indicating if you will use Female/Engaged (column 1) or Male/Married (column 2). In the 2nd section the radio buttons will select which values to use for First Attended and Shareholder Lapse.'),
(2963, 278, 'More event page formatting', 1, 104, 1, 1, '2012-05-21 23:10:48', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-05-22', '2012-12-16', 'Queued', NULL, NULL, '1. The blue bar that says "Unbound Meeting" and all of the listings below it that say "Unbound Meeting 	Sunday...."\r\n2. make the "Description" label align with the top of the description field. It looks like it is aligned to the bottom now.'),
(2964, 278, 'Pending Events changes', 1, 104, 1, 1, '2012-05-21 23:16:20', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-05-22', '2012-12-16', 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'Make "Reject/Approve" 2 separate columns with radio buttons instead of a single check box. We should probably have a 3rd column labelled "Pending" that will be the default fo all of the events listed.\r\n\r\nThen you can get rid of the drop down list labelled "With Selected:" at the bottom.'),
(2965, 278, 'Report page changes', 1, 104, 1, 1, '2012-05-21 23:24:38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-05-22', '2012-12-16', 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'I don''t like this page at all. Instead of having a separate form for each report with it''s own date fields and submit button I think it is better to have a single form where you select the date range and then select the desired report from a drop down list.\r\n\r\nAlso implement the date picker that is used in the Vine application here with the same calendar icon instead of the "Select" buttons.'),
