(2968, 312, 'Migrate policy number', 1, 145, 1, 1, '2012-05-22 15:49:01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-06-05', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'I have added a field in the insurancepolicy table for the policy number. We want to stop saving this in the insuranceinfo table and start saving it to the insurancepolicy table instead.'),
(2969, 312, 'Check rights on viewing covered for a policy hide from subscription', 1, 145, 1, 3, '2012-05-22 18:07:12', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-07-05', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'I don''t think that they should be able to view who is covered by a policy unless they are on it. This is kind of working because you can not access the policy to view who is covered. Still, I think the GetInsuranceCoveredProfiles() should implement correct security.\r\n\r\nAll GetInsuranceCoveredProfiles() requires for security currently is ValidateInsuranceViewRights which does not return a view/edit value.\r\n\r\nInvestigate this and let me know what you find.\r\n\r\nUPDATED****\r\n-If you can only view yourself then you probably should not be able to see who else is covered by any policy.'),
(2971, 285, 'Document Rights', 1, NULL, 1, 1, '2012-05-22 18:11:40', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-06-18', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2972, 312, 'Check insurance policy removal rights for edit-self privs', 1, 145, 1, 2, '2012-05-22 18:19:04', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-07-03', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'I think if a person can only edit themself then they should only be able to remove a policy if they are the only one covered by it.\r\n\r\nInvestigate this and let me know what you find.\r\n\r\nWe only store "Who is covered" Right now by taking their full name and storing it in the database. It is not linked to the account in anyway so if a profile''s name changes, the "Covered" doesn''t.'),
(2973, 325, 'Insurance policy name is unique on the web server', 1, NULL, 1, 2, '2012-05-22 19:01:38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-06-27', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2975, 321, 'Check rights updating emergency contact info', 1, 145, 1, 2, '2012-05-22 20:11:38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-07-10', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'See the rights doc for correct rights. It is located in the doc folder of the project.\r\n\r\nInvestigate this and let me know what you find.\r\n\r\nUpdating-\r\nSubscription rights --Yes\r\nEdit All  ------------Shown---    Yes                    [Yes]\r\nEdit All -------------Hide------- MUST FOLLOW:\r\n    1.the contact is one of the users contacts\r\n    2. the user is the last person to edit the contact\r\n    3. the user has assigned the contact to at least one profile (not necessarily their own)\r\nEdit Self ------------Either-------Must be listed on contact\r\n\r\n\r\nSub - Hidden - [Works -- 7/9]\r\nSub - Show    - [Works -- 7/9]\r\nEAll - Hidden - IsContact -\r\nEAll - Show    - [Done]\r\nESel - Hidden - [Works]\r\nESel - Hidden - IsContact - [Works 7/10]\r\nESel - Show -  [Works 7/10]\r\nENon - Hidden - IsContact - [Works]\r\nENon - Hidden - [Done 7/10]\r\nENon - Show  - [Done 7/10]\r\n\r\n\r\nProblems: Updating with edit all/ sub rights and a hidden by me contact returns insuffient rights'),
(2976, 306, 'Changes to device activation', 1, 145, 1, 1, '2012-05-25 13:01:13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-06-06', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'When we create a new account we currently create an activation key. We actually need three fields:\r\n\r\nDevice ID: 32 characters (divided into 4 groups of 8 characters each)\r\nKey: 24 chcracters (divided into 4 groups of 6 characters each)\r\nActivation code: maybe 10 characters\r\n\r\nThe Device ID needs to be unique. The others do not have to be. You should ask Mark Woods if he has ideas about how to create these fields.\r\n\r\nWe need to save all 3 of those in the phonenumnber table and email all 3 of them to the owner of the phone.'),
(2977, 181, 'Load member info after a person is selected.', 1, 104, 1, 3, '2012-05-28 03:32:50', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'People are loaded into either the left or right hand column with the id1 and id2 variables like this:\r\n\r\nhttp://joel.vineyardcincinnati.com/vine/MergePeople.php?id1=18493\r\nhttp://joel.vineyardcincinnati.com/vine/MergePeople.php?id2=257610\r\n\r\nWhat you need to do is cause the page to read the information from the db and show it on the page in the correct column. You can copy the query from memberinfo.php. It will probably get most of the fields. \r\n\r\nBecause you can only select 1 person at a time and you need to have 2 people in the page to do a merge you are going to have to remember the the 1st person who was selected when making the 2nd selection. I suggest using $_SESSION[''MergeID1''] and $_SESSION[''MergeID2''] to keep track of both id numbers so you can know what people to load.'),
