(2981, 329, 'Why do we reopen the database on every page?', 1, NULL, 1, 3, '2012-05-29 19:39:14', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-07-03', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'Can''t we use getInstance to get an instance of the same db object? \r\n\r\nIt is working on EmergencyMedicalInformation.java.\r\n\r\nAlso it is better to make a new database as paet of opening the database instead of having a separate createDataBase().'),
(2982, 193, 'Upload test pdf files into the database', 1, 104, 1, 2, '2012-05-30 12:54:21', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-06-12', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'In order to protect the files downloaded for the paid tests from being accessed by people who did not pay we want to store these files in the database. I added a blob field to the examfiles table to store the files. \r\n\r\nSearch online and see if you can find code to save a pdf file into a database table and also to extract it from the database table. When you find something let''s have a chat.'),
(2983, 186, 'When you delete a task it should take you back to the previous page.', 1, 104, 1, 4, '2012-05-30 13:05:33', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-09-10', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'After you delete a task it keeps you on he task editing page as if the deletion was not performed. It is misleading because the task no longer exists but you are still editing it. \r\n\r\nThere is already some logic that should return you to the last listing page that (it could be Tasks by Project, Tasks by Priority, ...). Whatever logic it is using to return to the previous page when editing a task should be followed when deleting also. My guess is the logic is already there but commented out for some reason.\r\n\r\nIf you have a question then please ask.'),
(2985, 286, 'Email address showing up twice when editing profiles', 1, 145, 1, 1, '2012-05-30 13:21:28', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-06-18', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'This is the problem: \r\n\r\nThe email address is saved in the profile table for a profile because it is part of their log in credentials. Emergency contacts also have an email address (recently added). To do that I added a record in the contactfields table for email address. Now the email address shows up twice on the profile editing page (once because it is part of the profile table and once because of the contactfields record). \r\n\r\nThink about this and propose a solution to me. Don''t fix it yet. Just propose a solution and we will discuss it.'),
