(3045, 286, 'Seperate timestamps for email and state', 1, 145, 1, 1, '2012-06-20 16:41:48', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-06-22', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'I added 4 new datetime fields in the profile table. They should be set like this:\r\n\r\nnameupdated: set if any of the 4 name fields are changed\r\nprivsupdated: set if any of the 3 rights fields are changed\r\nemailupdated: set if the email address is changed\r\nstateupdated: set if either the state OR country are changed\r\n\r\nupdated can do what it does now.\r\n\r\nProbably the easiest way to do this is to update the UpdateProfile procedure to read the profile record and do a comparison with the new values to see what is changed. You will also need to change the CreateProfile procedure and whatever else we use to assign the rights.'),
