(3055, 252, 'Volunteers not being checked in - 430', 1, 104, 1, 1, '2012-06-25 01:00:32', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-06-27', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'If you attempt to check in a volunteer it appears to be working but apparently not. After you check them in if you change rooms and then go reselect the room where you checked in the volunteer the volunteer list is empty. I think probably the js is adding the name to the list even though they are not successfully being added in the database. When you click a room button it reloads the volunteer list from the db and then the list is empty.\r\n\r\nYou made a change to this page relating to how we select the volunteer groups and the volunteers. I suspect that you broke this when you did that. I put an alert statement on line 301 to see what is going on and the group id is "undefined". I am guessing that when we select the volunteer group to get the roster it should be saving the group id somewhere and it is not.\r\n\r\nAlso, we should not be manipulating the list of volunteers in the room directly. After we do a check in we should just reload the list from the db. I think we made a similar change on the child check-in page. That way if the volunteer is not successfully checked in it will not show them on the right side erroneously.'),
