(3081, 193, 'Matching Questions', 1, 147, 1, 4, '2012-07-04 11:08:44', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-08-15', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'This is going to be the most complicated because unlike all of the other question types there are actually 2 lists of selections. Are you familiar with what I mean by matching? You have 2 lists, normally side by side. One list might say:\r\n\r\n1. USA\r\n2. Philippines\r\n3. Japan\r\n\r\nThe other list might say:\r\n___ New York City\r\n___ Tokyo\r\n___ Moscow\r\n___ Manila\r\n___ Kyoto\r\n___ Washington DC.\r\n\r\nYou would have to put 1 next to Washington DC, 2 next to Manila and 3 next to Tokyo. The other 3 need to be left blank.\r\n\r\nI am not sure how we want to represent that in the database, if we want to have 2 tables for the4 2 different lists or if we just want to add an extra field or 2 in the examchoices. I am leaning toward the 2nd one just because it makes it easier to maintain the relationship between the correct a matches. But we would have to randomize the order when showing the question to a customer. If we had them in 2 tables we could just show them in the prescribed order but we have to worry about implementing a foreigh key so that Washington DC is never removed unless USA is first removed. \r\n\r\nYour thoughts? Talk to me about this before you do it.'),
(3082, 195, 'Order type questions', 1, 147, 1, 3, '2012-07-04 11:15:09', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-07-22', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'Ordering questions give a list of options like a normal test except that instead of indicating which is correct you would order the selections (such as from largest to smallest or from best to worst). \r\n\r\nChange the test editor so that you can create questions and indicate their correct order instead of having radio buttons to indicate which is correct. Probably we should have input fields where they can indicate the numbers representing the correct order of the answers.. The question type selection should enable the input fields and hide the radio buttons or whatever is implemented for the prior selected question type.  \r\n\r\nI have added an "answer" field in the examchoices table. Store the order for each question there.'),
(3083, 195, 'Add a field to select question type on the test editing page', 1, 147, 1, 1, '2012-07-04 11:20:09', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-07-05', NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, 'When editing a test the first field needs to be question type. It should have a drop down list with the following selections: \r\n\r\n1 Correct\r\nTrue / False\r\nMultiple Correct\r\nOrdering\r\nMatching\r\n\r\nYou will need to modify the datatype field in the examqstn table to store this new field. change it to a varchar(1) and put either:\r\n\r\n1 = 1 Correct\r\nO = Ordering (letter O, not zero)\r\nM = Matching\r\nT = True / false\r\nX = Multiple Correct\r\n\r\nThe drop down list for the question type is going to have to execute some javascript to hide and show different fields when a selection is made. More on that in other tasks...'),
(3084, 195, 'Multiple correct question type', 1, 147, 1, 2, '2012-07-04 11:40:11', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-07-22', NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, 'Multiple correct questions work like the current questions except that there is more than one correct answer. \r\n\r\nChange the test editor so that there are check boxes instead of radio buttons to indicate which is correct. The question type selection should enable the check boxes and hide the radio buttons or whatever is implemented for the prior selected question type.  \r\n\r\nI have added an "answer" field in the examchoices table. Store 1 if the question is checked and null if it is unchecked.'),
