(3167, 321, 'Emergency Contact New Contact Making Duplicates on refresh', 145, 145, 145, 1, '2012-08-28 20:12:44', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-08-29', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'After adding an emergency contact, if the user refreshes the page it causes a duplicate entry to be submitted. \r\n\r\n2 options:\r\n\r\n1. Redirect header to same page\r\n2. Redirect header to middle page, redirect page back to emcontacts\r\n3. Variable to tell if form is new or old\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n1. caused infinite redirect loop (maybe i did it wrong?) And would have caused problems with the back button.\r\n2. Too much logic to move to a different page.\r\n3. WORKS!!!!\r\n           ----Creates a timestamp when loading page, sets it to userdata and also a hidden field called FormDateTime. When the page is submitted these number will match up and the contact will be added to the database. Then when it loads the page again, the timestamp changes in the session and on the current pages form.   \r\n\r\nThis means when the page is refreshed and it looks at the old form data, it will use the old form timestamp (''FormDateTime'') but the userdata timestamp will have been changed and prevent the contact from being added.'),
