(3250, 349, 'Test taking security - 90', 1, NULL, 1, 3, '2012-10-23 19:13:09', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'let me change both of these settings in the CMS:\r\n\r\n1. set the maximum # of tests in any account to be 70 (our policy is still 10 x # of questions) however if someone puts a robot on our system to keep starting tests it could bring it down.\r\n\r\n2. if more than 50 questions are answered in any 60 second period (they have a robot on it) then end the users'' session with some message of ''Your Session Has Timed Out'' and email admin@tests.com a message with their email, date/time, test id, and other data you have about that session. IF this happens twice in the same day, end the session with the ''Your Session has Ended'' message and automatically ''inactivate'' (see #3 below because it is related) their account\r\n\r\n3. give us the ability to manually ''inactivate'' (not delete) an account on the client edit pages (http://tests.com/dbadmin/testsalesview.php?id=912#clientedit )'),
(3251, 126, 'Compare listings page - 91, 97', 1, 104, 1, 2, '2012-10-23 19:19:07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-10-25', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'Got to a search result page, check a few listings, add them to the basket, then click the link at the bottom to compare the listings...\r\n\r\n1. first column heading should be Test Item like omn the search results page\r\n\r\n2. the top part (where the logo, search box and login link are) of the compare page should be like the top of this page: http://www.tests.com/contact-us .\r\n\r\n3. Make the heading "My Test Listings"\r\n\r\n4. make the checkmark that is in the first column of the headings have a ''text title'' such that when you hover over it, it says "Check off listings that you want to compare and/or email to a friend."'),
(3252, 200, 'Test author editing - 92', 1, NULL, 1, 3, '2012-10-23 19:20:16', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2012-11-30', NULL, 'Queued', NULL, NULL, 'please add a new CMS file that we can update with 8 fields:\r\n* author ID#\r\n* author last name\r\n* author first name\r\n* author email\r\n* author category 1 (pull down menu)\r\n* author category 2 (pull down menu)\r\n* author category 3 (pull down menu)\r\n* notes\r\n\r\nthen on the exam definition pages, allow us to use a pull down menu to assign the test to any author in the author file.\r\n\r\nand on the exam questions page, allow us for any question to choose another author from the list. this will allow us to identify instances where quesitons are added to an original test by new test authors because we may move to a question bank model where each question bank has more than one test author'),
